        "title": "feat: add shared terminal primitives",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add one public `@openclaw/libterminal` package with runtime-specific subpath exports\n- publish terminal protocol v2, bounded streaming, Ghostty browser rendering, Node PTY/stdin helpers, Worker WebSocket bridging, and reusable test doubles\n- add OpenClaw governance, hardened autoreview, CodeQL, stale automation, and tag-driven npm OIDC release workflow\n\n## Compatibility And Security\n\n- runtime-neutral protocol plus isolated browser, Node.js, and Worker entry points\n- preserve ordered forwarding, backpressure, cancellation, close-reason sanitization, and explicit teardown semantics\n- disable reviewer filesystem, shell, web, plugin, MCP, and agent tools; reject oversized review bundles\n- no credentials, private paths, private hosts, or sensitive logs included\n\n## Validation\n\n- [x] `pnpm check` (40 Vitest tests, types, lint, build, packed-package verification)\n- [x] `pnpm test:browser` (real pinned Ghostty WASM smoke)\n- [x] `python3 .agents/skills/autoreview/tests/test_autoreview_hardening.py` (19 tests)\n- [x] `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --self-test-engine-isolation`\n- [x] `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --stream-engine-output` (clean, no actionable findings)\n- [x] tests added or updated when behavior changed\n- [x] Browser, Node.js, and Worker impact considered\n- [x] `CHANGELOG.md` updated\n\n## Release Bootstrap\n\nThe npm name is still unclaimed. Before merging/tagging, a maintainer must publish a minimal temporary `@openclaw/libterminal@0.0.0` package and configure npm trusted publishing for `.github/workflows/release.yml`. Do not manually publish this branch's `0.1.0`.\n\n## Release Note\n\nAdds the shared terminal foundation intended to replace duplicated terminal protocol, streaming, Ghostty, PTY, and Worker glue in Crabfleet and MultiCodex.",
